<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Plunge Patrol</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Plunge Patrol tracks King County lake-beach conditions, organized beach by beach for cold-water swimmers.">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,600;9..144,700&family=Manrope:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/styles/app.css">
  <script type="module" src="/assets/scripts/app.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>

  <header class="site-shell">
    <div class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">King County lake beaches</p>
      <h1>Plunge Patrol</h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        Plunge Patrol organizes King County swim-beach data into beach-specific panels for cold-water swimmers.
        Each module loads on its own, keeps its own failure state, and uses the county&rsquo;s official public feeds.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <p>Temperature is shown as the latest recorded value. Safety always comes from the county&rsquo;s official beach status.</p>
        <p>Outside the May to September monitoring season, some beaches may show &ldquo;No recent data&rdquo; with an older recorded temperature.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="main-content">
    <beach-app></beach-app>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <p>Data sources: public ArcGIS layers from King County beach status and water temperature monitoring.</p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://kingcounty.gov/en/dept/dnrp/nature-recreation/parks-recreation/king-county-parks/water-recreation/swimming-beach-bacteria-temperature">Official county page</a>
    </p>
    <p class="site-footer__disclaimer">
      Plunge Patrol is provided for informational purposes only. Water conditions can change quickly, this app may lag official updates,
      and you assume all risk for any decisions or activity based on this information. Always verify current conditions with the official
      county source and use your own judgment before entering the water.
    </p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
